Business came to standstill in Machakos town on Tuesday as rival candidates launched their campaigns for the senatorial by-election after they were cleared by the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC).
Three of the 10 candidates, Mutua Katuku (Maendeleo Chap Chap), Urbanus Ngengele (UDA) and Agnes Kavindu (Wiper) turned the presentation of nomination papers into a popularity contest.



