“Wiper picked a person who cannot match the kind of wit and courage required to fight for the interests of Machakos people. She will even struggle to catch the Speaker’s attention during debates” said the former senator.
Mr Muthama, the interim chairman of the new party United Democratic Alliance associated with Deputy President William Ruto, urged voters to elect his candidate as he began the crusade against his ex-wife.
Barely an hour later, Kavindu responded angrily telling off her ex-husband over his remarks, and demanding that he respects her as the mother of his children.
She revisited her marital woes saying she has suffered immensely after their messy divorce, but insisted she deserves a second chance in life and the right to pursue her political ambitions.
“What should a woman do after being thrown out of her matrimonial home by her husband? Is one supposed to just die after divorce?” she posed to the cheering crowd while struggling to fight back tears during an emotional speech at Mulu Mutisya Gardens.
She urged Muthama to restrain from personal attacks by avoiding making their divorce a campaign issue and accord her an equal measure of respect.





Kavindu, who was picked by President Uhuru Kenyatta as a member of the defunct Building Bridges Initiative (BBI) taskforce, sought to insulate her ex-husband from being attacked by her campaigners saying she still respects him as the father of her children.



